[Sounds very like _S. abortusovis_ outbreaks that used to occur (and still
might) in central Devon in the UK every year. As reported, the vaccination
advice appears confused. Blaming seagulls is one thing, proving it
something else. This infection probably makes use of many routes besides
the 'obvious'. - Mod.MHJ]
